ossing partitions as\nintroduced by Kreweras (now an important tool in several parts of mathematics,\nfor example in free probability theory). We review some classical problems\nwhich are related to the maximal chains in NC: to count labeled trees as well\nas parking functions. The combinatorics of the Dynkin case A is just the\ncombinatorics of the Catalan numbers; in an appendix, we discuss the nature of\nclassical Catalan combinatorics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Feb 2015 19:07:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 24 Aug 2015 20:56:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-08-26"}
