 be caused by mechanisms related to the\nstripping process: the existence of an massive central black hole or internal\nkinematics that are out of equilibrium due to the stripping event. Given the\nobserved dynamical-to-stellar mass ratio we suggest that S999 is an ideal\ncandidate to search for the presence of an overly massive central black hole.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Feb 2015 20:59:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-24"}
